*Galax urceolata* (Poir.) Brummitt
det. Michelle Gaynor, 1 June 2021

GATES COUNTY: Merchant Millhopper State Park,
Lassiter Trail right past the main pond. Elev. 13 – 15 m.
Co-occurring species include *Ilex opaca*, *Hexastylis minor*,
and *Fagus grandifolia*. Surrounded by lots of leaf debris.
No old flowers. Mostly new leaves. Very patchy
populations.

Lat. 36.43689902 Long. -76.69245902 Datum: WGS84
coll. Michelle Gaynor # 55 1 June 2021 *(handwritten)*

North Carolina Division of Parks and Recreation, Scientific
Research and Collecting Permit, 2021_0524.
